## Next.js

### Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router) — check `package.json` for version
- **Rendering:** Server Components by default, `'use client'` for Client Components
- **CSS:** Tailwind CSS v4 or CSS Modules
- **Build:** Turbopack (dev), Webpack/Turbopack (production)

### Key Patterns

- **Server Components** (default) — no client JS, direct DB/API access, async components
- **Client Components** — `'use client'` directive at top of file, for interactivity/hooks
- **Server Actions** — `'use server'` for mutations, form handling, data writes
- **Route Handlers** — `app/api/*/route.ts` with `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE` exports
- **Middleware** — `middleware.ts` at project root for auth guards, redirects, rewrites
- **Metadata** — `export const metadata` or `generateMetadata()` in `layout.tsx`/`page.tsx`
- **Loading/Error UI** — `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx` per route segment

### Conventions

- Prefer Server Components — only add `'use client'` when hooks or interactivity are needed
- Server Actions for form submissions and data mutations (not API routes)
- Environment variables: `process.env.*` (server), `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` prefix for client
- Images via `next/image` component (automatic optimization)
- Links via `next/link` component (client-side navigation)
- Self-host fonts via `next/font` — no external CDN (GDPR, performance)
- Dynamic routes: `[slug]` folders, catch-all with `[...slug]`
- Parallel routes: `@modal`, `@sidebar` for simultaneous layouts

### Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # Start dev server (Turbopack)
npm run build    # Production build
npm run start    # Start production server
npx next lint    # Run ESLint with Next.js rules
```
